<body>
    <h1>Lab Walkthrough: Installing a Motherboard</h1>
    <p>In this lab, we will be selecting and installing a motherboard for a new computer system, connecting the case cables, and the power supply connectors. Follow the steps below to complete the installation.</p>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 1: Select the Motherboard</h2>
        <p>Ensure the motherboard meets the following requirements:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>16x PCI Express slot for video card support</li>
            <li>M.2 storage support</li>
            <li>Support for 64-bit processors</li>
            <li>Dual-channel memory support</li>
            <li>Support for up to 64 GB of memory</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 2: Prepare the Work Area</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensure you have a clean, static-free work area.</li>
            <li>Gather all necessary tools (e.g., screwdriver).</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 3: Install the Motherboard</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Open the computer case.</li>
            <li>Locate and screw in the standoffs to the appropriate positions in the case.</li>
            <li>Align the motherboard with the standoffs and I/O shield at the back of the case.</li>
            <li>Carefully place the motherboard into the case, ensuring all ports align with the I/O shield.</li>
            <li>Secure the motherboard with screws.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 4: Connect the Computer Case Cables</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Power Switch:</strong> Connect the power switch cable to the motherboard's power switch pins.</li>
            <li><strong>Reset Switch:</strong> Connect the reset switch cable to the reset switch pins on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>Power LED (3-1 pin):</strong> Connect the power LED cable to the appropriate pins on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>HDD LED:</strong> Connect the HDD LED cable to the HDD LED pins on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>Speaker:</strong> Connect the speaker cable to the speaker pins on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>Front Fan:</strong> Connect the front fan cable to the motherboard's fan header.</li>
            <li><strong>Rear Fan:</strong> Connect the rear fan cable to the appropriate fan header on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>USB (Black cable - 2.0):</strong> Connect the USB 2.0 cable to the USB 2.0 header on the motherboard.</li>
            <li><strong>Front Panel Audio:</strong> Connect the front panel audio cable to the motherboard’s audio header.</li>
            <li><strong>USB 3.0:</strong> Connect the USB 3.0 cable to the USB 3.0 header on the motherboard.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Step 5: Connect the Power Supply Connectors</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>CPU Power:</strong> Connect the 4-pin or 8-pin CPU power connector to the motherboard’s CPU power socket.</li>
            <li><strong>Main Motherboard Power:</strong> Connect the 24-pin main power connector to the motherboard’s main power socket.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
        <h2>Final Checks</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensure all connections are secure.</li>
            <li>Verify that there are no loose screws or components.</li>
            <li>Close the computer case.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
